"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-olympics-paris-2024-tony-estanguet-b2594809.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Estanguet acknowledged that the Games were not perfect and organisers had issues to resolve  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 414, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Paris 2024president Tony Estanguet insisted he has \\\"no regrets at all\\\" about how theOlympicshave unfolded despite some controversies at the Games.\", \"from\": 415, \"to\": 585, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 439, \"end\": 444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3391685469974444e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Asthe Games concludes with the closing ceremonyat the Stade de France, with theUSA coming out on top in the final medal table, Estanguet has had time to reflect on the past fortnight.\", \"from\": 587, \"to\": 770, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The rain-disrupted opening ceremony proved especially divisive, with Paris organisers apologising to religious groups over a scene which they feltmocked Leonardo da Vinci's painting 'The Last Supper'.\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 971, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 840, \"end\": 845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3391685469974444e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 924, \"end\": 941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3383976021584794e-14, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The early days of the Games were blighted by bad weather while several training sessions in the River Seine for the triathlon and marathon swim events were cancelled after failing water quality tests.\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 1173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1069, \"end\": 1080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's triathlonwas pushed back 24 hours but all events got the green light, ultimately vindicating the decision of authorities to spend 1.4 billion euros (\\u00a31.2 billion) to try to clean up the river.\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1377, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Estanguet admitted there have been some imperfections but he pointed to an Olympic record 9.5 million tickets being sold as one of the reasons these Games can be regarded as an overwhelming success.\", \"from\": 1379, \"to\": 1577, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Estanguet said in his closing speech: \\\"The evening of the opening ceremony, when the athletes paraded on the Seine, when C\\u00e9line Dion sang The Hymn to Love from the balcony of the Eiffel Tower, when the Olympic Cauldron rose up into the Parisian skies, a momentum began.\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1688, \"end\": 1693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.579416760055944e-14, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1700, \"end\": 1711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"C\\u00e9line Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}, {\"begin\": 1781, \"end\": 1797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.187548830478711e-20, \"text\": \"Olympic Cauldron\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And from the next morning, with the first medals, a wave started building.\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 1925, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This wave took over the country, carried the whole world in its wake and went beyond anything we could imagine.\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 2037, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We wanted strong images, our competition venues will go down in the history of the Games.\", \"from\": 2038, \"to\": 2127, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We wanted excitement, we got passion.\", \"from\": 2128, \"to\": 2165, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We wanted to be inspired, we got L\\u00e9on Marchand.\", \"from\": 2167, \"to\": 2215, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2201, \"end\": 2214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999997803538704, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"L\\u00e9on Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Together, we have experienced Games like nothing the world has seen before.\\\"\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2292, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Estanguet, who won three Olympic golds in the canoe slalom between 2000 and 2012, said: \\\"It would be a little bit like a spoiled brat saying 'I have got regrets about the Olympic Games', it's not the case.\", \"from\": 2294, \"to\": 2499, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Yes, I was an athlete and I am a perfectionist, I can be a little bit of a nitpicker.\", \"from\": 2501, \"to\": 2587, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I know things were not perfect.\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2619, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We had issues, things that needed to be fine-tuned.\", \"from\": 2620, \"to\": 2671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There are always things that could be improved and we have had issues day-in day-out to resolve.\", \"from\": 2673, \"to\": 2770, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But if someone told me on the eve of the opening ceremony of how things would go, I would have said 'sign me up'.\", \"from\": 2772, \"to\": 2886, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's wonderful, it's a huge success, a collective success, incredibly so.\", \"from\": 2887, \"to\": 2960, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"France has rallied together to pull off this edition of the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 2962, \"to\": 3037, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2963, \"end\": 2969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7725389205972429, \"rank\": 0.2932787197819461, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am so proud of the success story.\", \"from\": 3038, \"to\": 3073, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have no regrets at all.\\\"\", \"from\": 3074, \"to\": 3100, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris is preparing to pass the Olympic torch this weekend to 2028 hosts Los Angeles and the French capital will now turn its focus to the Paralympics, starting later this month.\", \"from\": 3102, \"to\": 3279, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3102, \"end\": 3107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3391685469974444e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3174, \"end\": 3185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999022293, \"rank\": 3.832786272457399e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 3194, \"end\": 3200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.514185985553934, \"rank\": 0.6024174455608552, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have got the same level of ambition for the Paralympic Games,\\\" Estanguet added.\", \"from\": 3281, \"to\": 3364, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Paralympic Games will extend this celebration.\", \"from\": 3365, \"to\": 3416, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is a very big ambition from the Paris 2024 teams to succeed in these first Paralympic Games organised in France.\\\"\", \"from\": 3418, \"to\": 3538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3457, \"end\": 3467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.766766353677516e-26, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3530, \"end\": 3536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7725389205972429, \"rank\": 0.2932787197819461, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3540, \"to\": 3676, \"entities\": []}]}"